1.1 Definition:
Spring Data Access is a part of the Spring Framework that provides consistent, simplified, and exception-safe access to data sources such as:
Relational Databases
ORM frameworks (JPA/Hibernate)
JDBC
NoSQL databases

ðŸ“Œ Goal: Reduce boilerplate code and handle DB interactions uniformly.

1.2 Why Spring Data Access:
Eliminates repetitive JDBC code
Unified exception hierarchy
Easy transaction management
Integrates with JDBC, JPA, Hibernate
Works seamlessly with Spring Boot

2. DATA ACCESS OPTIONS IN SPRING
=================================

2.1 JDBC (Spring JDBC):
Definition:
Spring JDBC simplifies database access using JdbcTemplate.

2.2 ORM (Spring ORM):
Supports ORM frameworks:
JPA
Hibernate
MyBatis

ðŸ“Œ Most real-time projects use Spring Data JPA.

2.3 Spring Data JPA:

Provides repository abstraction on top of JPA.
